  {
    "hotel_id": "236879",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/heiwadai-hotel-tenjin/hotel/fukuoka-jp.html",
    "name": "Heiwadai Hotel Tenjin",
    "detail": "Very friendly staffs. Good breakfast. You have a choice of continental or Japanese. (It's not a buffet.) Either is good. Corridor smelt a bit funky. It didnt quite bother me, but my mum hated it. Stayed in a double bed room. The bed is nice and clean. Rooms a bit small. There is a balcony over the window but it's all connected with other rooms. No mozzie net on the window. Couldnt open the window, but air-con works fust fine. Water pressure is a bit weak, a bit hard to adjust to the perfect water temperature. But not that major of a problem. Bus stops right behind the building. Ask for a bus info at the front. They provide a table with destination, fare, time, etc. About 10 minutes walking to the Tenjin station. Not really a convenient spot for touring down town Fukuoka. But with a bus pass or if you dont walking a bit, not a problem at all. ",
